1":"1651","1585":"1585","1650":"1650","18 September 1601":"18 september 1601","5 December 1604":"5 december 1604","1605":"1605","1604":"1604","Bideford,Devon,England":"Bideford, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bideford, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Bideford, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bideford, Devon, England":"Bideford, Devon, England","England":"England","Bideford, Torridge district, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bideford, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"May 7, 1571–Abt 1650":"7 May 1571–about 1650","1571–1650":"1571–1650","1567–1670":"1567–1670","1604–1644":"1604–1644","1605–Male":"1605–Deceased","1550–Male":"1550–Deceased","1550":"1550","1670":"1670","1571":"1571","May 7, 1571":"7 May 1571","1644":"1644","1600":"1600","1567":"1567","18 SEP 1601":"18 September 1601","about 1605":"about 1605","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","Abt 1650":"about 1650","1651":"1651","1585":"1585","1650":"1650","18 September 1601":"18 September 1601","5 December 1604":"5 December 1604","1605":"1605","1604":"1604","Bideford,Devon,England":"Bideford, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Bideford, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Bideford, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Bideford, Devon, England":"Bideford, Devon, England","England":"England","Bideford, Torridge district, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bideford, Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wynslade","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Winslade (Hants) or Winslade in East Putford (Devon). The Hants place-name was  <i>Winesflot</i> in 1086,  <i>Winslode</i> in 1399, and had forms in  <i>-a-</i> from the Tudor period. The Devon place-name was recorded as  <i>Wydeslade</i> in 1360 and  <i>Wynslade</i> by 1567."],"variants":[{"name":"Winslet","meanings":["English: apparently a late variant of   Winslade  . Compare James Winslett, 1746, Wm Winslade, 1796 in   IGI   (Farnham, Surrey); Samuel Winslade, 1774, John Winslet, 1785 in   IGI   (Richmond, Surrey)."]}]},{"name":"Johan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Older Scottish spelling of <b>Joan</b> , which was traditionally pronounced as two syllables."],"variants":[{"name":"Jens","meanings":["Mainly Danish: variant of   Johan ."]},{"name":"Jöns","meanings":["Mainly Danish: variant of   Johan ."]},{"name":"Jan","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]},{"name":"Jon","meanings":["Simplified spelling of   John   or a short form of   Jonathan .  The name is borne by the Canadian singer  Jon Vickers  (  b. 1926 ) and the American actor  Jon Voight  (  b. 1938 )."]},{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":13,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":15,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":28,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":48,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705213,"age":70,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Johan Wynslade was born on 7 May 1571, in Bideford, Devon, England